('20862', '1', 'Combine 16 cups water and pork in very large deep pot. bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Using sieve or slotted spoon, remove pork pieces from broth and discard. DO AHEAD: Broth can be made 2 days ahead. Cool slightly. Chill uncovered until cold, then cover and keep chilled.'),
('20862', '2', 'Return broth to boil. Season lightly with salt and pepper.'),
('20862', '3', 'Add greens to broth by large handfuls, allowing greens to wilt slightly before adding more. Cover and boil gently over medium heat just until greens are tender, about 10 minutes for mustard greens and 20 minutes for turnip greens or kale.'),
('20862', '4', 'Drain, reserving cooking liquid.'),
('20862', '5', 'Transfer greens to serving bowl. Moisten generously with cooking liquid (reserve remaining cooking liquid for another use). Season to taste with salt and generous amount of pepper. Scatter onion over, if desired, and serve.'),
('20863', '1', 'Peel the turnips and coarsely grate them into a bowl.  Toss with salt and vinegar.  Cover and set aside at room temperature for 1 hour.'),
('20863', '2', 'Cut the rhubarb into 2-inch pieces.'),
('20863', '3', 'Cut each piece lengthwise into 3 strips.  Wash in cold water and drain.'),
('20863', '4', 'Place the rhubarb in a large saucepan and toss with the sugar.  Cook the rhubarb over moderate heat for 5 minutes, or until the rhubarb begins to wilt but still is slightly crisp.'),
('20863', '5', 'Drain the grated turnips in a colander or strainer, pressing out as much liquid as possible.  Fold the turnips into the rhubarb and cook until heated through.'),
('20863', '6', 'Serve immediately.'),
('20863', '7', 'var article'),
('20863', '8', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('20863', '9', 'article'),
('20863', '10', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('20864', '1', 'To make the pastry: Toss the butter or the fat in the flour until coated.'),
('20864', '2', 'Add the salt.'),
('20864', '3', 'Add a little ice water and bring the dough together with your hands, sprinkling no more than a few teaspoons of water.  On a well-floured surface, shape the dough into a square.  Sprinkle more flour onto the square to prevent sticking later. then roll out the dough into a rectangle approximately 1/2 inch thick.  Fold the rectangle lengthwise in the shape of an envelope. then roll and repeat.  Dust with flour as needed.  Repeat this procedure at least 3 or more times, preferably 5 times, taking care not to warm or soften the dough too much as you roll.  Cover the pastry with plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator.'),
('20865', '1', 'Heat oil in a stockpot over medium-high heat. Sprinkle beef with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.'),
('20865', '2', 'Add beef to pan. saut 10 minutes or until browned.'),
('20865', '3', 'Remove from pan.'),
('20865', '4', 'Add onion, bay leaves, and thyme sprigs to pan. Cover, reduce heat, and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('20865', '5', 'Uncover. stir in tomato paste. Increase heat to medium-high.'),
('20865', '6', 'Add carrot, turnips, barley, 4 garlic cloves, and mushrooms. saut 3 minutes.'),
('20865', '7', 'Add beef, 1/2 teaspoon salt, water, broth, Worcestershire, and beer. bring to a boil. Reduce heat. simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Discard bay leaves and thyme sprigs.'),
('20865', '8', 'While stew is simmering, trim beets, leaving root and 1 inch stem on each. scrub with a brush.'),
('20865', '9', 'Place in a medium saucepan, and cover with water. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 35 minutes or until tender.'),
('20865', '10', 'Drain. rinse with cold water.'),
('20865', '11', 'Drain. cool. Leave root and 1 inch stem on each beet. rub off skins.'),
('20865', '12', 'Cut each beet into 6 wedges.'),
('20865', '13', 'Combine parsley, thyme leaves, and 1 garlic clove. Ladle about 2 cups stew into each of 6 bowls. Top each serving with 3 beet wedges, about 1 1/2 teaspoons parsley mixture, and 1 teaspoon horseradish.'),
('20866', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('20866', '2', 'Put all vegetables (including garlic) except sweet potatoes into a very large bowl (or two large ones). put sweet potatoes in a separate bowl.'),
('20866', '3', 'Drizzle bowls generously with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Toss gently with your hands to coat. then spread half of mixed vegetables on two large baking sheets. Break up 3 rosemary sprigs and sprinkle over vegetables.'),
('20866', '4', 'Roast vegetables 15 minutes. Stir gently with a metal spatula if they are sticking.'),
('20866', '5', 'Add half of the sweet potatoes to pans. Continue roasting, stirring vegetables every 15 minutes if necessary and changing positions of pans to ensure even browning, until vegetables are browned and tender, 40 minutes to 1 1/4 hours.'),
('20866', '6', 'Remove from oven and set aside. Repeat with remaining half of mixed vegetables, sweet potatoes, and 2 1/2 rosemary sprigs.'),
('20866', '7', 'Pour vegetables onto a serving platter and season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('20866', '8', 'Garnish with remaining sprig of rosemary and serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('20872', '1', 'Position 1 rack in top third and 1 rack in bottom third of oven and preheat to 375F. Spray 2 large rimmed baking sheets with nonstick spray. Melt butter with olive oil in small saucepan over medium-low heat.'),
('20872', '2', 'Combine red beets, large pinch of thyme, large pinch of savory, and 1 tablespoon melted butter mixture in medium bowl. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Turn beets out onto 1 side of 1 prepared sheet.'),
('20872', '3', 'Combine all remaining vegetables and herbs, garlic, and remaining butter mixture in large bowl. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Divide vegetable mixture between prepared baking sheets.');